4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the homesteads of certain
6 individuals whose annual income is below a fixed amount
7 are exempt from ad valorem tax.
8 This bill would increase this annual income cap.
9 This bill would also extend this exemption to
10 the unremarried widow or widower of those individuals.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 Relating to ad valorem tax; to amend Sections 40-9-19,
18 40-9-19.1, and 40-9-21, Code of Alabama 1975, regarding
19 homestead exemptions; to allow the unremarried widow or
20 widower of certain individuals to claim the exemption; to
21 increase the adjusted income cap; and to make nonsubstantive,
22 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
23 current style.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. Sections 40-9-19, 40-9-19.1, and 40-9-21,
26 Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
